			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2024</a> paper:</span><br><i>AI Effects on Research and Education: A Programming and Software Language Perspective (Panel)</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/RalfLämmel.html">Ralf Lämmel</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3687997.3698125">10.1145/3687997.3698125</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6g.html"><span class="tagM">T6G: Socio-technical</span></a><ul><li> The panel centers on socio-technical impacts of LLMs on research, education, and programming practice.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4g.html"><span class="tagL">T4G: AI-for-SLE</span></a><ul><li> It explicitly discusses large language models as a disruptive technology relevant to AI-for-SLE and tooling.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6d.html"><span class="tagL">T6D: Synergies</span></a><ul><li> The discussion connects perspectives across communities (PL, compilers, education) to identify shared challenges.
</li></ul></li></ul>
